'''Inferential theory of learning''' ('''ITL''') is an area of [[machine learning]] which describes inferential processes performed by learning agents.  ITL has been developed by Ryszard S. Michalski in 1980s.  In ITL [[Learning|learning process]] is viewed as a search ([[inference]]) through hypotheses space guided by a specific goal.  Results of learning need to be [[Data storage device|stored]], in order to be used in the future.

