'''Siobhan Roberts''' is a Canadian science journalist, biographer, and [[history of mathematics|historian of mathematics]]. Roberts did her undergraduate studies in history at Queen's University, and earned a graduate degree in journalism from [[Ryerson University]]. She has won a number of Canadian [[National Media Awards Foundation|National Magazine Awards]],{{r|rrj}} and she is the winner of the Communications Award of the [[Joint Policy Board for Mathematics]] "for her engaging biographies of eminent mathematicians and articles about mathematics".{{r|rrj|siam}}

Roberts is the author of:
*''King of Infinite Space: Donald Coxeter, the Man Who Saved Geometry'', about [[Harold Scott MacDonald Coxeter]] (Walker & Company, 2006),{{r|kis}} winner of the [[Euler Book Prize]] of the [[Mathematical Association of America]]{{r|euler}}
*''Wind Wizard: Alan G. Davenport and the Art of Wind Engineering'', about [[Alan Garnett Davenport]] (Princeton University Press, 2012),{{r|ww}} winner of the W. Gordon Plewes History Award of the [[Canadian Society for Civil Engineering]]{{r|csce}}
*''Genius At Play: The Curious Mind of John Horton Conway'', about [[John Horton Conway]] (Bloomsbury, 2015){{r|gap}}

